"""
extract_concepts.py
--------------------
PHASE 1: extract UMLS CUIs for every document.

Two modes (set MODE):
  "doc"  : ONE API call per document -- blobs joined into one text, sent once, and
           the concepts mapped back to each blob by character offset (verified
           against the surface text; offsets that don't reproduce it fall back to
           locating the surface). Fewer calls.
  "blob" : ONE API call per blob -- faithful, identical to extracting each blob on
           its own. Every blob of every doc runs in a single MAX_WORKERS-wide pool
           (deduped: identical blob text is called once and reused), with per-blob
           checkpoint + resume.
Documents/blobs run in parallel (MAX_WORKERS at a time). No PDFs opened.

Output pickle (keyed by the reconstructed_obj.pk key):

    { key: {
        "doc_id": "doc_101_sample_101",
        # ADDRESS (join back to sources / PDFs):
        "key": 101, "input_file": None, "sampling_id": "sampling_1",
        "sample_index": 101, "file_name": "sample_101.pdf",
        # metadata:
        "raw_document": "...", "category": "...", "pages": 2,
        "n_blobs": 17, "n_sections": 17, "n_chunks": 17,
        "chunks": [ {"i":0,"blob_index":0,"preview":"...","cuis":["C..."]}, ... ],
        "extracted_cuis": ["C...", ...],   # doc-level union
        "doc_secs": 41.2, "server_ms": {"extraction_ms":..,"matching_ms":..},
        "n_errors": 0, "complete": True,
      }, ... }

Recover text / PDF from an address:
    reconstructed_obj.pk[key]['reconstructed']['blobs'][blob_index]
    sampling_1_stats.pk['samples'][sample_index]
"""

